handNote.seg:
Nomina sacra; 
four lines (in both columns) in the incipit page (fol. 3r), divided into two groups, alternating with black lines;
some lines (one, two) at paragraph beginning on fols. 4va (ls. 15-16), 11ra (ls. 9-10), 18va (ls. 5-6), 24vb (l.16), 34ra (ls. 9-10);
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; 
elements of the punctuation signs;
the words “sanbat”, “lä-sanbat”;
names of the donors.
